        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many projects should a creative portfolio include?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Quality over quantity. 8-12 projects is the sweet spot for most creatives. Fewer than 6 suggests limited experience; more than 15 becomes overwhelming to browse. Each project should represent your best work - if a project doesn't make you proud, delete it. Organize by showing your strongest 3-4 projects first, then group the rest by category or client type. For students: 6-8 projects showcasing range and skills. For mid-career: 8-12 curated projects showing expertise and style. For senior creatives: 10-15 landmark projects with detailed case studies. Remember: you're judged by your weakest project. Curate ruthlessly. Update quarterly. Remove old work that no longer represents your current level or direction."
